 I'd be happy to help you write a simple C program that prints an increasing pattern of numbers. Here's an example using a for loop:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int i;
    for (i = 1; i <= 5; i++) { // Change the number 5 to the number of rows you want in your pattern
        printf("%d\n", i);
    }
    return 0;
}
```

This program will print the numbers from 1 to 5 (or any number you choose) on separate lines. If you'd like a different kind of increasing pattern, please let me know and I can help you modify the code accordingly.
